        "age upon outcome, outcome type, indate, outdate, animaltype (will only be looking at dogs), outtype, sex, color, and breed. We restrict our analysis to dogs by filtering the AnimalType variable. Indate and Outdate allow us to compute the length of stay, which is central to understanding shelter dynamics. Outtype serves as the primary outcome variable, indicating whether a dog was adopted, fostered, transferred, euthanized, or otherwise exited the shelter. Breed and color are included as categorical predictors, as physical characteristics may influence adoption likelihood or how long it might take for a dog to be adopted.\n",
        "  -  Descriptions of any shortcomings this dataset has with respect to the project: This dataset does not include any relevant information regarding an animal’s health or age, which is understandable because it is difficult to specifically pinpoint what a stray dog’s age is. Age is often a strong predictor of adoption likelihood, and health status may significantly impact both the dog’s length of stay and outcome type. \n",
