      "source": [
        "#### RQ2 EDA: Purebred vs. Mixed-Breed Status and Adoption Rates\n",
        "\n",
        "To investigate whether breed labeling influences adoption outcomes, we classify each dog as **Purebred** or **Mixed** based on its breed string. A dog is classified as mixed if its breed field contains indicators such as \"Mix\", \"/\", or \"Cross\"; otherwise it is classified as purebred. This binary collapse is motivated by the theoretical distinction between purebred preference and mixed-breed stigma documented in prior shelter research, and avoids the noise of comparing hundreds of inconsistent breed categories across shelters.\n",
        "\n",
        "All four datasets (Austin, Louisville, Sonoma, and Bloomington) are included. For each city, we compute the adoption rate for purebred and mixed-breed dogs separately, along with 95% confidence intervals derived from the standard error of a binomial proportion. We then test for statistical association between breed type and adoption outcome within each city using chi-square tests of independence."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "# RQ2 setup: classifying every dog as Mixed or Purebred based on its breed string,\n",
        "# filtering each dataset to dogs only, then combining all four cities into one dataframe\n",
        "# drop any rows where breed was missing (like \"Unknown\")\n",
        "\n",
        "import pandas as pd\n",
        "import numpy as np\n",
        "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
        "import seaborn as sns\n",
        "from scipy import stats\n",
        "\n",
        "def classify_breed(breed_str):\n",
        "    \"\"\"Classify a breed string as 'Mixed' or 'Purebred'.\"\"\"\n",
        "    if pd.isna(breed_str):\n",
        "        return 'Unknown'\n",
        "    b = breed_str.upper()\n",
        "    if 'MIX' in b or '/' in b or 'CROSS' in b:\n",
        "        return 'Mixed'\n",
        "    return 'Purebred'\n",
        "\n",
        "def build_rq2_subset(df, city_name, breed_col, outcome_col, adoption_label,\n",
        "                     species_col=None, species_label=None):\n",
        "    \"\"\"Filter to dogs, classify breed, and return a tidy DataFrame.\"\"\"\n",
        "    subset = df.copy()\n",
        "    if species_col is not None:\n",
        "        subset = subset[subset[species_col] == species_label]\n",
        "    return pd.DataFrame({\n",
        "        'city': city_name,\n",
        "        'breed_type': subset[breed_col].apply(classify_breed),\n",
        "        'adopted': (subset[outcome_col] == adoption_label).astype(int)\n",
        "    })\n",
        "\n",
        "austin_rq2 = build_rq2_subset(austin, 'Austin', 'breed', 'outcome_type',\n",
        "                               'Adoption', 'animal_type', 'Dog')\n",
